you know it was a good nap when you’re chilling like this

I have and will NEVER say that my Doberman isn’t friendly because…

1. She is extremely friendly. 
2. I don’t need to contribute to the stereotype that dobies, among other bully breeds, are vicious because it is such a false narrative. 

While I love stand-up and can appreciate the nature of this joke (honestly, I don’t want anyone I don’t know touching my beautiful, perfectly clean dog anyways), I always just say that she is in an active training session (which isn’t a lie) because we cannot keep leading people to believe these dogs can’t be friendly. 

IT’S THE OWNER NOT THE DOG‼️

I made it to my 3rd birthday! 🥹🥂

Getting diagnosed with Chronic Active Hepatitis (liver disease) at the age of one was less than ideal, but today, I officially beat my prognosis!

Most people think we are crazy for maintaining the treatment this dog requires but she is our family and is living her absolute best life. 

Having an awesome support system of friends, family and an incredible team of vets, @parkdaleahwaterloo (more family) also helps a lot too😉

Always advocate for those who don’t have a voice, and know that you’re doing everything you can. 

Happy 3rd Birthday, Cali Girl. You are so loved 🖤
